    "In contrast, additive models, including feed-forward neural networks, present a smoother transition.",
    "The results across each group for the final MLP models that best balanced accuracy and smoothness in results are presented in Table 4.",
    "Due to outliers present in the data, and heavy skewness towards zero claims, the fitted models failed to predict situations where claims had a very high frequency or severity, leading to lower maximum values.",
